Ask HN: Is there a DALL-E or library for image sets?
text:
does anybody here know where or how i can use a set of images to generate an image which represents the average of the set? like if i feed it 100 apples and wanted it to output a unique version of apple?

I do not know what this is called but that's the behavior I would like to implement if anyone knows which language/libraries support this kind of thing could you tell me in the comments please?

Git branch command triggered an Xcode license agreement?
text:
I ran a git branch command and I was triggered with an Xcode license agreement.

$ git branch

You have not agreed to the Xcode license agreements. You must agree to both license agreements below in order to use Xcode.

Press the 'return' key to view the license agreements at '/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Resources/en.lproj/License.rtf'

Xcode and Apple SDKs Agreement
